               <head>Grant;  Brampton, etc.; 1453</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename>, the prior</persName>, and <orgName key="org_105053">convent of Woodbridge</orgName> grant to
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Wyvyle</surname>, esq.</persName>, a certain 
                  annual rent or pension of £6 sterling for the term of his life, issuing out of their lands &amp;c. 
                  in the villages of <placeName key="place_105194">Brampton (Bramston)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_105438">Newbourne (Neuburne)</placeName>, and
                  <placeName key="place_105336">Hemley (Helmole)</placeName>. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_105544">Woodbridge</placeName>, <origDate when="1453-08-10">10 August, 31 Hen. VI (1453)</origDate><!--1452-09-01|1453-08-31-->. 
                  </p>
                     <p> [MS. Ch. Suffolk 246 was described as follows in 1878. That number is not now to be found, but the entry was probably mistaken duplication of the above entry.]
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Nicholas</forename>, the prior</persName>, and 
                        <orgName key="org_105053">convent of St. Mary of Woodbridge</orgName> confirm to 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Wyvyle</surname>, esq.</persName>, an 
                        annual pension of £6 for his life, issuing out of the manors of 
                        <placeName type="manor" key="place_105006">Brampton (Bramston)</placeName>, <placeName type="manor" key="place_105055">Haspley with Newbourne (Neuburne)</placeName>, and
                        <placeName type="manor" key="place_105035">Hemley (Helmole)</placeName>, co. Suffolk; and if
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Beatrice</forename>, wife of the said Robert</persName>, should survive him, 
                        she to have a pension of 4 marks. 
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_105544">Woodbridge</placeName>, <origDate when="1453-08-10">10 August, 31 Hen. VI (1453)</origDate><!--1452-09-01|1453-08-31-->. 
                     </p>
